&lt;p&gt;ThermalWorks LLC has an exciting opportunity for a &lt;strong&gt;Commissioning Project Engineer &lt;/strong&gt;to join the Startup &amp;amp; Commissioning team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is responsible for coordinating project timelines, attending scheduling and planning meetings, and ensuring that startup, integrated system testing (IST), and flush and fill activities are executed on schedule and to ThermalWorks standards. The Commissioning Project Engineer works closely with the mechanical install Project Manager to ensure seamless handoffs from installation through commissioning, and serves as the primary owner of flush and fill procedures in the field. The ideal candidate brings a solid mechanical/HVAC background — including piping systems and commissioning experience — combined with strong organizational and communication skills.&lt;/p&gt;
